WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.264
Previously on "Queen Sugar"...

00:03.307 --> 00:04.787
Nova: I'm gonna stage
a ring shout on the land.

00:04.830 --> 00:06.049
I just need to get
a couple corporations

00:06.093 --> 00:08.443
to feel the same way
about this place as I do.

00:08.486 --> 00:09.922
They will.

00:09.966 --> 00:12.055
Making money is exciting,
but it can't be your end goal.

00:12.099 --> 00:14.057
Think about what you're
putting out into the world.

00:14.101 --> 00:15.493
I'm selling
Black History Month.

00:15.537 --> 00:18.496
Plantains are my specialty.
My mom taught me.

00:18.540 --> 00:19.889
How is she?
She's good.

00:19.932 --> 00:22.152
You would tell me
if there was a problem, right?

00:22.196 --> 00:23.023
Vince?

00:23.066 --> 00:25.025
Be true to your own heart.

00:25.068 --> 00:28.115
I wanna understand what's
kept you away for so long.

00:28.158 --> 00:30.682
And I will tell you
when I'm ready.

00:30.726 --> 00:32.336
[ Laughs ]

00:32.380 --> 00:34.034
Man, I don't even know how you
got me in this pool right now.

00:34.077 --> 00:35.296
Just let go.
Just let go.

00:35.339 --> 00:38.516
Lift your feet up.
Okay. There you go.

00:39.387 --> 00:41.171
[ Laughs ]

00:41.215 --> 00:42.346
You did good, though.

00:42.390 --> 00:43.869
I told you
I don't know how to swim.

00:43.913 --> 00:45.132
[ Laughs ] Oh, wait.
No, wait, wait, come on.

00:45.175 --> 00:46.002
What?

00:46.046 --> 00:47.395
Here, I'll show you.

00:47.438 --> 00:51.312
You just let the water
hold you up.

00:54.489 --> 00:56.534
Alright.

00:56.578 --> 01:02.714
♪♪

01:02.758 --> 01:04.499
You got me?

01:04.542 --> 01:07.328
I got you.

01:07.371 --> 01:08.372
You sure?

01:08.416 --> 01:09.852
Mm-hmm.

01:09.895 --> 01:16.554
♪♪

01:16.598 --> 01:19.557
Come on.
Come on.

01:21.385 --> 01:24.258
All you have to do
is breathe.

01:24.301 --> 01:25.911
Just relax.

01:25.955 --> 01:31.569
♪♪

01:31.613 --> 01:37.097
♪♪

01:37.140 --> 01:38.402
♪ Dreams never die

01:38.446 --> 01:41.144
♪ Take flight
as the world turns ♪

01:41.188 --> 01:42.928
♪ Keep the colors in the lines

01:42.972 --> 01:44.930
♪ Take flight
as the world turns ♪

01:44.974 --> 01:46.758
♪ Keep the colors in the lines

01:46.802 --> 01:49.152
♪ Take flight

01:49.196 --> 01:51.241
♪ Dreams never die

01:51.285 --> 01:56.768
♪♪

01:56.812 --> 02:00.598
♪ Keep the colors in the lines

02:00.642 --> 02:04.036
♪ Keep the colors in the lines,
take flight ♪

02:04.907 --> 02:06.169
Blue: I'm sorry.

02:06.213 --> 02:08.215
I know you're disappointed
in me.

02:08.258 --> 02:09.607
Grandma's really mad.

02:09.651 --> 02:11.000
This is serious, Blue.

02:11.043 --> 02:13.133
Maybe being suspended
won't be so bad.

02:13.176 --> 02:14.873
I could come home early.

02:14.917 --> 02:16.832
I can't wait
to see you guys.

02:16.875 --> 02:17.963
I really miss you.

02:18.007 --> 02:20.052
He's really
buttering us up.

02:20.096 --> 02:22.098
Okay, look, I have to go
or I'll miss my flight.

02:22.142 --> 02:23.317
Bye, Mom.
Bye, Pops.

02:23.360 --> 02:25.145
-Bye, Blue.
-Catch you later, Blue.

02:25.188 --> 02:27.234
Don't forget,
Baby & Friends at 3:00.

02:27.277 --> 02:28.887
You know how expensive
those classes are.

02:28.931 --> 02:30.106
They don't do refunds.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.586
I got it.

02:31.629 --> 02:33.675
You have the doctor's number
in case anything comes up.

02:33.718 --> 02:35.329
I know it's on your phone,
but I also taped it

02:35.372 --> 02:36.808
to the fridge
just in case.

02:36.852 --> 02:39.115
Baby, tell Mommy
we got it.

02:39.159 --> 02:41.770
I cannot believe
Blue would do this.

02:41.813 --> 02:43.511
They might suspend him.

02:45.904 --> 02:47.819
Maybe we just
come with you.

02:47.863 --> 02:48.951
Make it a little
family trip.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.344
No, you need to be here.

02:50.387 --> 02:53.216
There's the auction,
the first harvest.

02:53.260 --> 02:55.523
I'll be back in time
for the potluck.

02:55.566 --> 02:57.177
[ Sighs ]
Maybe I just shouldn't go.

02:57.220 --> 02:59.179
Baby, go.
Look, we'll be here

02:59.222 --> 03:03.139
waiting for you
when you get back, alright?

03:03.183 --> 03:05.576
Go take care
of our little man.

03:05.620 --> 03:08.362
Pop quiz --
when is Baby & Friends?

03:10.364 --> 03:11.669
Ralph Angel, give me
your phone so I can --

03:11.713 --> 03:13.671
It's today.

03:13.715 --> 03:15.934
It's at 3:00, right?

03:15.978 --> 03:16.935
Right.

03:16.979 --> 03:19.764
I got this.

03:19.808 --> 03:22.680
Say bye.

03:22.724 --> 03:23.768
I'll see you later.

03:23.812 --> 03:25.074
Mm-hmm.

03:25.117 --> 03:26.728
[ Indistinct conversation
and laughter ]

03:26.771 --> 03:28.686
Sandy:
That's so funny.

03:28.730 --> 03:30.514
[ Laughter ]

03:30.558 --> 03:32.603
That tickles.

03:32.647 --> 03:33.604
[ Door opens ]

03:33.648 --> 03:35.563
[ Laughter ]

03:35.606 --> 03:37.826
Billie!

03:37.869 --> 03:39.871
I love that top.

03:39.915 --> 03:42.091
Good morning.Don't be too long.

03:42.134 --> 03:43.484
[ Squeals ]

03:45.007 --> 03:47.227
[ Clears throat ]

03:47.270 --> 03:49.620
Sorry, honey.
I thought you were --

03:49.664 --> 03:50.708
I thought you were out.

03:50.752 --> 03:52.057
No, no.
It's -- It's fine, Daddy.

03:52.101 --> 03:54.408
I mean, this is your house,
so...

03:54.451 --> 03:58.020
You guys seem, um --
seem really happy.

03:58.063 --> 03:59.239
Weren't you and Vince
supposed to be

03:59.282 --> 04:01.110
having breakfast
this morning?

04:01.153 --> 04:04.374
We did,
and it didn't go great.

04:04.418 --> 04:06.507
So, he's taking a walk.

04:12.339 --> 04:14.254
This is so hard.

04:14.297 --> 04:17.909
I mean, I don't even know
what to say anymore.

04:17.953 --> 04:21.086
Vince came all the way out here
to prove he cares.

04:21.130 --> 04:22.566
Let him.

04:22.610 --> 04:24.568
I'm different now.

04:24.612 --> 04:27.832
And this time apart has --
has changed me.

04:27.876 --> 04:28.920
[ Sighs ]

04:28.964 --> 04:30.879
It's changed us.

04:30.922 --> 04:32.141
[ Door opens ]

04:32.184 --> 04:33.273
Sandy: You know,
I'll wait in your room.

04:33.316 --> 04:34.709
I see you two are talking.

04:34.752 --> 04:36.580
No, no, Sandy, stay.

04:36.624 --> 04:38.408
Stay.
No, I insist.

04:38.452 --> 04:40.628
Look, I have to get out
of here anyway.

04:40.671 --> 04:42.891
Give you two your space.

04:42.934 --> 04:46.895
Are you sure
you don't need to talk?

04:46.938 --> 04:50.028
No, Daddy, I'm fine.
Thanks.

04:50.072 --> 04:52.030
♪♪

04:52.074 --> 04:54.163
[ Knock on door ]

04:54.206 --> 04:57.949
♪♪

04:57.993 --> 05:00.038
Oh, baby,
I'm still setting up.

05:00.082 --> 05:01.170
Give me about an hour.

05:01.213 --> 05:03.607
I'm with social services.

05:03.651 --> 05:06.044
I'm looking for
a Joaquin Avila.

05:06.088 --> 05:08.003
I heard he might
be working here?

05:08.046 --> 05:09.439
What's this all about?

05:09.483 --> 05:10.919
[ Sighs ] I've spent
the last three weeks

05:10.962 --> 05:13.530
looking for Joaquin
and his brother Dante.

05:13.574 --> 05:16.011
They haven't been in school,
and I have reason to believe

05:16.054 --> 05:20.711
there's no adult supervision
in the house.

05:20.755 --> 05:21.930
Well, he's not here,

05:21.973 --> 05:24.846
but if I hear anything,
I will let you know.

05:24.889 --> 05:26.326
Please, this is serious.

05:26.369 --> 05:28.676
It starts with
skipping school, and...

05:28.719 --> 05:30.330
doesn't end well.

05:33.507 --> 05:39.077
♪♪

05:39.121 --> 05:41.166
What about all this --
what is --

05:41.210 --> 05:43.734
Mo, would you talk some sense
into Cardale?

05:43.778 --> 05:46.563
Now, we all need to
put our land in a trust

05:46.607 --> 05:49.523
so what happened to Parthena
won't happen again.

05:49.566 --> 05:50.741
He's right.

05:50.785 --> 05:52.395
The Land Trust --
it will hold them at bay.

05:52.439 --> 05:55.790
My property been in my family
for three generations,

05:55.833 --> 05:58.358
and it's gonna stay in there
three more.

05:58.401 --> 06:00.011
So you're just thinking
about yourself?

06:00.055 --> 06:01.230
Is that all this is about?

06:01.273 --> 06:03.188
-No!
-Fellas, listen up. Come on.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.625
I thought we gotta
work together, right?

06:04.668 --> 06:06.104
Man, tomorrow, they're
auctioning off

06:06.148 --> 06:07.628
Ms. Parthena's land.

06:07.671 --> 06:09.369
We said we want to help,
right?

06:09.412 --> 06:11.196
Now, this is the chance.

06:11.240 --> 06:12.850
Ralph Angel,
what you going on about?

06:12.894 --> 06:16.332
We're going to that auction,
but we bid against each other,

06:16.376 --> 06:18.421
box out the other bidders.

06:18.465 --> 06:20.162
We get your land back.

06:20.205 --> 06:21.685
We got enough money pooled,

06:21.729 --> 06:25.341
plus we got some funds
left over, right?

06:25.385 --> 06:26.777
You think it could work?

06:26.821 --> 06:28.170
We got more than enough.

06:28.213 --> 06:30.694
I mean,
if we all work together.

06:30.738 --> 06:31.782
Is everybody in?

06:31.826 --> 06:33.828
-I'm in.
-Yep.

06:33.871 --> 06:41.226
♪♪

06:41.270 --> 06:43.403
I wouldn't miss it.

06:44.534 --> 06:46.275
[ Chuckles ]
Count me in.

06:46.318 --> 06:47.363
Uh-huh.

06:47.407 --> 06:48.973
[ Laughter ]

06:49.017 --> 06:50.018
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

06:50.061 --> 06:52.107
Chris: Yo, Zane.

06:52.150 --> 06:55.066
What's up?

06:55.110 --> 06:56.328
What's good, man?

06:56.372 --> 06:59.114
Chris, what's up, bro?
Yeah, man.

06:59.157 --> 07:02.334
♪♪

07:02.378 --> 07:04.032
What the hell was that?

07:04.075 --> 07:05.337
What was what?

07:05.381 --> 07:07.557
The guys.
They just, like, ignored me

07:07.601 --> 07:09.820
when I tried
to dap them up.

07:09.864 --> 07:12.257
Well, you're only as good
as your last sell.

07:12.301 --> 07:14.912
I told you, those political
photos you posted

07:14.956 --> 07:16.697
didn'tsell.

07:18.046 --> 07:22.485
Okay, so if I'm not
selling all the time,

07:22.529 --> 07:24.444
then I'm just out?

07:24.487 --> 07:26.837
Yeah, I told you upfront.

07:26.881 --> 07:28.752
You came to me
to sell your art, right?

07:28.796 --> 07:29.753
Yeah.

07:29.797 --> 07:32.843
Well, you wanna know
what sells?

07:32.887 --> 07:34.584
What's hot.

07:38.022 --> 07:41.330
This girl turned her ex's
text messages into an NFT.

07:41.373 --> 07:43.245
Micah:
Yo, and it sold for 35K?

07:43.288 --> 07:44.768
-Mm-hmm.
-Damn.

07:44.812 --> 07:45.813
And this one.

07:45.856 --> 07:47.945
It's a Boomerang
of LeBron James.

07:47.989 --> 07:49.947
And it sold for 208K.

07:49.991 --> 07:50.948
Sheesh.

07:50.992 --> 07:52.950
Your dad's an NBA star.

07:52.994 --> 07:54.299
Got something like that?

07:54.343 --> 07:57.346
I don't wanna put my exes
on blast, so let me see.

08:01.568 --> 08:04.135
Holy shit, that's what
I'm talking about.

08:04.179 --> 08:05.920
This is perfect.

08:05.963 --> 08:07.965
Yo, you post this with your
pedigree, it's gonna sell.

08:08.009 --> 08:09.663
No. No way.

08:12.404 --> 08:14.885
Yo, I gotta get
out of here, man.

08:14.929 --> 08:16.626
I'm behind
on this assignment.

08:16.670 --> 08:19.150
Rahad wants us to take
an evocative photo

08:19.194 --> 08:21.326
of a fascinating
stranger.

08:21.370 --> 08:23.067
Sounds artsy.
After you're done,

08:23.111 --> 08:24.634
maybe your dad can
introduce you to LeBron

08:24.678 --> 08:26.506
and you can
sell something.

08:26.549 --> 08:28.943
[ Scoffs ] Yeah.

08:28.986 --> 08:34.731
♪♪

08:34.775 --> 08:37.647
I got the stuff
for the co-op potluck tonight.

08:38.648 --> 08:41.390
This, I think,
is for you.

08:43.914 --> 08:46.656
Social worker came by
looking for you.

08:46.700 --> 08:48.876
Did you tell her
I worked here?

08:48.919 --> 08:50.834
No, I did not.

08:50.878 --> 08:52.662
But I think
you need to tell me

08:52.706 --> 08:55.056
what the hell
is going on right now.

08:55.099 --> 09:01.366
♪♪

09:01.410 --> 09:03.064
I'm sorry, Miss Violet.

09:05.196 --> 09:06.720
It's my mom.

09:06.763 --> 09:09.636
A couple weeks ago,
she didn't come home,

09:09.679 --> 09:10.941
and ever since
we were younger,

09:10.985 --> 09:12.856
she told us that
if she didn't come home,

09:12.900 --> 09:16.164
then ICE got her
and we should hide.

09:16.207 --> 09:18.688
Oh, Joaquin.

09:22.387 --> 09:24.564
Why didn't you
come to me?

09:24.607 --> 09:27.871
They told us that they'd
separate us in foster care

09:27.915 --> 09:31.571
and that we'd disappear,
that they could never find us.

09:32.876 --> 09:37.228
♪♪

09:37.272 --> 09:40.188
Do you know
where you mama is?

09:40.231 --> 09:41.798
Mexico.

09:41.842 --> 09:44.366
She called,
and she's coming back.

09:44.409 --> 09:47.195
We just have to stay put.

09:47.238 --> 09:48.892
It's not right.

09:48.936 --> 09:51.678
Separating families.

09:51.721 --> 09:54.419
Well, so where is
your brother?

09:57.422 --> 09:59.120
Joaquin?

10:01.470 --> 10:04.516
I want to see
where y'all are staying.

10:04.560 --> 10:06.127
Show me.

10:06.170 --> 10:09.913
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

10:09.957 --> 10:12.307
[ Siren wailing ]

10:12.350 --> 10:20.358
♪♪

10:20.402 --> 10:23.013
Dante.
It's okay to come out.

10:24.972 --> 10:26.669
Violet: Oh, baby.

10:30.499 --> 10:31.674
What happened?

10:31.718 --> 10:34.721
He got into a fight
at school.

10:36.331 --> 10:38.507
Y'all got any family
around here?

10:38.550 --> 10:41.945
No.
It's just us.

10:41.989 --> 10:43.643
Okay.

10:45.775 --> 10:47.647
Alright.

10:47.690 --> 10:50.475
So, uh, Dante,
pack your stuff,

10:50.519 --> 10:52.390
whatever you need.

10:52.434 --> 10:53.522
You're going home with me.

10:53.565 --> 10:54.741
We'll figure out
the rest later.

10:54.784 --> 10:56.133
Joaquin:
But we have to stay here.

10:56.177 --> 10:57.657
Our mom is coming back.

10:57.700 --> 10:59.528
We'll find some way
to contact her,

10:59.571 --> 11:03.227
but for now,
we're going home.

11:03.271 --> 11:06.535
♪♪

11:10.713 --> 11:12.410
Your mama thought
we wasn't gonna be on time,

11:12.454 --> 11:13.847
but look at us.

11:13.890 --> 11:18.025
[ Toys beeping
and playing music ]

11:18.068 --> 11:20.375
Toine.

11:20.418 --> 11:21.985
Hey, what you doing here?

11:22.029 --> 11:23.073
Man.

11:23.117 --> 11:24.161
You got all swole on me.

11:24.205 --> 11:26.163
-[ Laughs ]
-It's good to see you.

11:26.207 --> 11:27.643
Good to see you, too.

11:27.687 --> 11:28.949
Man, you gotta stay ready,
you know what I mean?

11:28.992 --> 11:30.602
These kids might look young,
but any of them

11:30.646 --> 11:32.953
try to bully my kid,
they're gonna get dealt with.

11:32.996 --> 11:33.997
[ Laughs ]

11:34.041 --> 11:35.825
-Hey, Tru.
-What up, Uncle Toine?

11:35.869 --> 11:37.392
Oh, my God.
You in trouble, man.

11:37.435 --> 11:38.828
She looks smart.

11:38.872 --> 11:40.351
She gonna have you wrapped
around her finger in no time.

11:40.395 --> 11:42.527
She already does.

11:42.571 --> 11:45.705
What's up, little man?
You got so big.

11:45.748 --> 11:47.228
Mm-hmm. Man, it goes fast,
I'm telling you.

11:47.271 --> 11:49.796
Shoot, we was trying for years
to get pregnant.

11:49.839 --> 11:52.146
Four rounds of IVF,
and then finally,

11:52.189 --> 11:53.756
this here's
our million-dollar baby.

11:53.800 --> 11:55.192
Man, he's perfect.

11:55.236 --> 11:57.368
I know you and the missus
must be proud.

11:57.412 --> 11:59.022
Swoled up and proud.Mm-hmm.

11:59.066 --> 12:00.632
Oh, brother,
look at this doll.

12:00.676 --> 12:01.895
You see this?

12:01.938 --> 12:03.635
Man, he carries this thing
everywhere.

12:03.679 --> 12:04.854
I have to sneak it out
from under him

12:04.898 --> 12:06.203
just to wash it
after he's asleep.

12:06.247 --> 12:08.989
You know how Blue was.
Couldn't let go of Kenya.

12:09.032 --> 12:10.207
Oh, yeah.
How's he doing?

12:10.251 --> 12:11.382
He's alright.

12:11.426 --> 12:13.036
Darla's with him
in DC right now.

12:13.080 --> 12:14.081
Yeah?

12:14.124 --> 12:16.039
Got in a little bit
of trouble.

12:16.083 --> 12:18.607
I just don't like him
not being so close.

12:18.650 --> 12:20.609
Yeah, I bet.

12:20.652 --> 12:22.306
Hey, man, I'm so glad
you're here.

12:22.350 --> 12:24.482
Usually me and Darla
are the only Black folks.

12:24.526 --> 12:25.788
[ Chuckles ]

12:25.832 --> 12:27.485
Now you, and another
Black father at that?

12:27.529 --> 12:28.835
We about to blow
some minds, brother.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.488
Let's show them
how it's done, huh?

12:30.532 --> 12:32.621
Come on.You ready, baby girl?

12:32.664 --> 12:34.014
Come on.

12:34.057 --> 12:36.233
-You ready to show some stuff?
-How y'all doing?

12:36.277 --> 12:37.800
We right here.
Yeah.

12:37.844 --> 12:40.281
Come on, baby.
Oh.

12:40.324 --> 12:42.631
Alright.
This your spot.

12:42.674 --> 12:45.068
Wait, so you gotta show me
what we doing.

12:45.112 --> 12:46.853
It's my first time, bro.

12:46.896 --> 12:50.334
Oh, man, it's pretty easy.
All you gotta do is clap.

12:50.378 --> 12:53.033
Let's go.
We gotta clap.

12:53.076 --> 12:54.774
That's all
I'm supposed to do?

12:54.817 --> 12:56.732
-A little shoulder.
-Okay, we can handle that, huh?

12:56.776 --> 12:58.647
You okay, baby?

12:58.690 --> 13:00.170
They weren't teaching us
what we needed --

13:00.214 --> 13:04.696
It's still illegal to hack
into the school's server.

13:04.740 --> 13:08.135
So when he comes in,
you apologize.

13:08.178 --> 13:10.311
[ Door opens ]

13:11.268 --> 13:14.924
Mrs. Bordelon, I appreciate
you coming all this way.

13:14.968 --> 13:16.665
Of course.

13:18.232 --> 13:21.626
We understand that Blue found
the history lessons lacking,

13:21.670 --> 13:24.586
but hacking into the system
is unacceptable.

13:25.761 --> 13:28.068
Blue, do you have something
that you would

13:28.111 --> 13:30.810
like to say
to Principal Jacobs?

13:36.337 --> 13:38.165
In our class,

13:38.208 --> 13:41.821
we learned a quote
from Walt Whitman --

13:41.864 --> 13:44.084
"Do I contradict myself?

13:44.127 --> 13:47.391
Very well,
then I contradict myself.

13:47.435 --> 13:49.306
I am large.

13:49.350 --> 13:52.832
I contain multitudes."

13:52.875 --> 13:55.225
We've been on the ground.

13:55.269 --> 13:56.531
Assata Shakur taught us

13:56.574 --> 13:59.664
that there was nothing to lose
but our chains.

13:59.708 --> 14:01.275
We've been in the sky.

14:01.318 --> 14:03.843
Bessie Coleman was the first
Black woman,

14:03.886 --> 14:07.324
the first Indigenous woman,
to hold a pilot's license.

14:07.368 --> 14:12.503
Mae Jemison took us
to space way back in 1992.

14:12.547 --> 14:15.898
All these names
we never hear about.

14:15.942 --> 14:18.292
We contain multitudes.

14:18.335 --> 14:20.685
And this school is not
teaching any of it.

14:20.729 --> 14:23.514
There are multiple ways
of addressing your criticism,

14:23.558 --> 14:24.994
Mr. Bordelon.

14:25.038 --> 14:27.214
Virtual breaking and entering
is not one of them.

14:27.257 --> 14:31.740
Blue may not have gone
about this the right way.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.310
But he is right.

14:36.353 --> 14:39.748
These icons
all broke the rules

14:39.791 --> 14:41.532
to make progress.

14:41.576 --> 14:45.232
Are you doing anything
to address the curriculum?

14:45.275 --> 14:46.537
It hasn't been discussed.

14:46.581 --> 14:49.714
Well, Blue was
a summer-school student here,

14:49.758 --> 14:51.716
and he improved
your curriculum

14:51.760 --> 14:53.196
by sharing
historical information

14:53.240 --> 14:56.156
that was missing
from your lesson plans.

14:56.199 --> 14:59.724
What he did
should be rewarded,

14:59.768 --> 15:01.509
not punished.

15:01.552 --> 15:07.515
♪♪

15:07.558 --> 15:09.647
What happened
to a phone call?

15:09.691 --> 15:11.214
I mean, you couldn't call
to let me know

15:11.258 --> 15:16.045
you bringing home two whole
human beings to stay with us?

15:16.089 --> 15:18.918
After I saw
how they was living,

15:18.961 --> 15:20.484
there was nothing
to talk about.

15:20.528 --> 15:24.880
Vi, this is the same kid
who wrecked your diner.

15:26.621 --> 15:29.232
We all got a past.

15:29.276 --> 15:32.409
And we're all better
than our worst day.

15:36.631 --> 15:37.980
Well, how long
they staying?

15:38.024 --> 15:39.721
I don't know yet.

15:39.764 --> 15:41.592
Let's just give it
a couple or days

15:41.636 --> 15:42.767
and go from there.

15:42.811 --> 15:45.118
Right now,
we're all they got.

15:48.730 --> 15:50.427
They need us.

15:50.471 --> 15:55.432
♪♪

15:55.476 --> 15:59.567
Never underestimate the love
of a Bordelon woman.

15:59.610 --> 16:01.177
Come here.

16:01.221 --> 16:08.315
♪♪

16:10.012 --> 16:12.797
Look, we've had --
no, we have

16:12.841 --> 16:14.103
a good life together,
Billie.

16:14.147 --> 16:15.452
If we're really
being honest,

16:15.496 --> 16:17.585
we've just kind of been
going through the motions.

16:17.628 --> 16:19.630
Well, I like the motions.

16:19.674 --> 16:22.546
Alright, look, remember
our late-night strategy sessions

16:22.590 --> 16:25.419
when we first met, huh,
that would turn into --

16:25.462 --> 16:26.898
Me on the desk.

16:26.942 --> 16:28.378
Mm-hmm.Calling on God.

16:28.422 --> 16:30.990
Yeah.

16:31.033 --> 16:33.818
And then we'd talk.

16:33.862 --> 16:36.212
All night.

16:36.256 --> 16:38.780
Be each other's
sounding board.

16:38.823 --> 16:42.784
Talk about our dreams,
our future,

16:42.827 --> 16:45.482
house, kids.

16:45.526 --> 16:49.443
Those were yourdreams
about our future.

16:49.486 --> 16:53.186
When Lila went to college
and it was just us,

16:53.229 --> 16:55.623
I realized
how much I gave up.

16:55.666 --> 16:57.755
You gave up?

16:57.799 --> 16:59.931
What'd you give up?

16:59.975 --> 17:02.412
You know I wanted to be
a lawyer, Vince, come on.

17:02.456 --> 17:05.415
I asked you a hundred times if
you wanted to go back to school,

17:05.459 --> 17:09.680
and a hundred more
if you wanted to get married.

17:09.724 --> 17:12.205
Don't revise things.

17:12.248 --> 17:14.337
I felt stuck.

17:14.381 --> 17:16.035
I did.

17:16.078 --> 17:17.340
And it wasn't
because of you.

17:17.384 --> 17:19.038
It was because of me.

17:19.081 --> 17:22.345
I mean, I-I thought I went
from being a bad daughter

17:22.389 --> 17:24.043
to a bad friend
to a bad mother,

17:24.086 --> 17:27.002
and I didn't want to be
a bad wife.

17:27.046 --> 17:28.917
I was stuck in my head.

17:31.485 --> 17:34.357
And then I came here,

17:34.401 --> 17:36.403
and...

17:39.580 --> 17:42.931
...I realized I wasn't
a bad daughter or a bad friend.

17:42.974 --> 17:48.893
♪♪

17:48.937 --> 17:51.070
I was taken advantage of.

17:55.726 --> 17:57.337
I was...

17:59.643 --> 18:01.950
I was assaulted,

18:01.993 --> 18:04.605
and, um...

18:04.648 --> 18:06.737
abused,

18:06.781 --> 18:10.350
and I was...

18:10.393 --> 18:13.527
disbelieved
and dismissed.

18:13.570 --> 18:16.704
The last six months I've just
been kind of, you know,

18:16.747 --> 18:19.707
digging through
all of that.

18:19.750 --> 18:22.492
'Cause, I mean, who am I

18:22.536 --> 18:27.106
when I find out everything
I thought I wasisn't true?

18:27.149 --> 18:29.369
You know, I mean...

18:29.412 --> 18:33.068
maybe I'm better
than what I thought.

18:33.112 --> 18:36.854
Look what I missed,
punishing myself.

18:36.898 --> 18:45.428
♪♪

18:45.472 --> 18:50.216
Baby, I never gave you
all of me.

18:50.259 --> 18:53.567
I never gave you everything.

18:53.610 --> 18:56.831
I never wanted
to let anyone,

18:56.874 --> 19:00.356
let alone you, fully in.

19:00.400 --> 19:02.010
You see?

19:02.053 --> 19:06.014
I was punishing myself,
and you in the process.

19:08.103 --> 19:11.454
And that can't be undone.

19:11.498 --> 19:15.110
It has to be fixed
inside.

19:18.026 --> 19:21.203
That's what I'm doing here,
Vince.

19:21.247 --> 19:23.031
That's what I need you
to let me do.

19:23.074 --> 19:30.778
♪♪

19:30.821 --> 19:32.954
I'm sorry.

19:34.869 --> 19:37.306
Hey, man, look, I'm -- I'm sorry
we been so out of touch,

19:37.350 --> 19:39.700
but that one just takes up
all our time, you know?

19:39.743 --> 19:41.615
It's all good, bro.

19:41.658 --> 19:44.139
I'm right there with you,
working two jobs,

19:44.183 --> 19:46.489
just trying
to make it happen.

19:46.533 --> 19:48.883
Yeah, man,
I-I heard about the farm.

19:48.926 --> 19:50.667
You good?

19:50.711 --> 19:52.191
Man, working it out.

19:52.234 --> 19:53.844
What about you
and them boys?

19:53.888 --> 19:55.063
Cops still
treating you right?

19:55.106 --> 19:58.284
Actually, I resigned.

19:58.327 --> 20:00.329
I mean, after the last
two years,

20:00.373 --> 20:02.810
then becoming a dad,
changed my whole perspective

20:02.853 --> 20:05.508
on what I'm willing to risk
every day, you know?

20:05.552 --> 20:07.249
I feel you.

20:07.293 --> 20:09.208
Changed everything for us,
too, really.

20:09.251 --> 20:10.252
You know,
when I told my wife

20:11.558 --> 20:12.559
that I was gonna quit my job
with no plan "B,"

20:12.602 --> 20:13.690
I thought
she was gonna kill me.

20:13.734 --> 20:14.952
-Of course.
-Yeah.

20:14.996 --> 20:17.825
But after she cussed me out,
she asked me,

20:17.868 --> 20:19.261
"What do you love to do?"

20:19.305 --> 20:22.090
Do what you love,
it don't feel like work, right?

20:22.133 --> 20:24.223
Mm-hmm.

20:24.266 --> 20:25.702
I don't know, man,
I was a good cop,

20:25.746 --> 20:27.138
but I didn't love it.

20:27.182 --> 20:29.271
I wanna leave something
for my kids, you know,

20:29.315 --> 20:31.621
make a difference.

20:31.665 --> 20:33.144
[ Clears throat ]

20:33.188 --> 20:35.886
Figure out
what that is yet?

20:35.930 --> 20:37.236
Well, I started volunteering

20:37.279 --> 20:39.150
with these trans kids
in the city.

20:39.194 --> 20:41.370
And my wife started
to come and join me.

20:41.414 --> 20:43.111
Now we run the center
together.

20:43.154 --> 20:44.330
Man, you been
figuring it out.

20:44.373 --> 20:46.070
Come on, man.
That's what's up.

20:46.114 --> 20:47.724
Congratulations, bro.Appreciate you, bro.

20:47.768 --> 20:49.509
No doubt.

20:49.552 --> 20:50.727
Thank you, bro.

20:50.771 --> 20:52.163
Hey, man, but you on yours,
too, right?

20:52.207 --> 20:54.122
When can I get
my farm-fresh delivery?

20:54.165 --> 20:55.732
Get that family-and-friends
discount, okay?

20:55.776 --> 20:56.820
Need some kale, huh?

20:56.864 --> 20:58.518
-Yes, I do.
-I got you.

20:58.561 --> 21:00.084
Alright,
and I like to hear it.

21:00.128 --> 21:01.303
Come on.

21:01.347 --> 21:03.566
Well, listen,
you're coming back, right?

21:03.610 --> 21:05.133
I'll be back.

21:05.176 --> 21:06.482
Yeah, we gotta show these
white girls what's going down.

21:06.526 --> 21:07.744
Man, come on.
You know how we do.

21:07.788 --> 21:09.746
That's it, man.

21:09.790 --> 21:11.574
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

21:11.618 --> 21:16.144
♪ Sunlight,
I can see it in your eyes ♪

21:16.187 --> 21:18.277
♪♪

21:18.320 --> 21:21.192
Micah: It reminds me
of Kennedi Carter's work.

21:21.236 --> 21:22.846
Did Rahad tell you that?

21:22.890 --> 21:25.371
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah. Busted.

21:25.414 --> 21:28.461
When I saw you standing here,
I wanted to come up and talk.

21:28.504 --> 21:30.114
I didn't know
how to break the ice.

21:30.158 --> 21:31.768
Well, that's a good start.

21:31.812 --> 21:33.509
Her work is stunning.

21:33.553 --> 21:36.164
Yeah, it is.

21:36.207 --> 21:38.166
It is.
Hey, I'm Micah.

21:38.209 --> 21:39.907
-Nice to meet you, Micah.
-You, too. You, too.

21:39.950 --> 21:42.301
I'm actually, uh,
taking a class here with Rahad.

21:42.344 --> 21:45.434
He told us to take a photo
of a fascinating stranger,

21:45.478 --> 21:47.784
capture their story,
so I was hoping, maybe --

21:47.828 --> 21:50.657
He's stealing my whole act.
That was one of my assignments

21:50.700 --> 21:52.746
when Rahad was
one of my students.

21:52.789 --> 21:55.183
-Oh, you're a photographer?
-I am.

21:55.226 --> 21:57.054
-Wow.
-"Fascinating stranger."

21:57.098 --> 21:59.056
What makes me fascinating
to you?

21:59.100 --> 22:00.754
I mean, take a look.

22:00.797 --> 22:04.192
You got all this style,
this swag, this vibe.

22:04.235 --> 22:07.500
Like, I don't know,
you just -- you pop.

22:07.543 --> 22:09.197
You're a smooth talker,
huh?

22:09.240 --> 22:11.634
[ Chuckles ]

22:11.678 --> 22:17.597
♪♪

22:17.640 --> 22:20.034
Wait, is this yours?

22:20.077 --> 22:21.557
Wow.

22:21.601 --> 22:23.864
It's great.
It's great.

22:23.907 --> 22:26.257
I was -- I was here
the other day just, you know,

22:26.301 --> 22:28.608
staring at her eyes.

22:28.651 --> 22:31.132
You get lost
in those eyes.

22:31.175 --> 22:33.221
I did many times.

22:34.527 --> 22:37.225
[ Sighs ]
Love of my life.

22:37.268 --> 22:39.836
♪ Baby, we gonna have
a situation ♪

22:39.880 --> 22:41.490
♪♪

22:41.534 --> 22:45.364
Hey, you think I can, uh,
take a photo of you two?

22:45.407 --> 22:48.018
-Sure.
-[ Chuckles ]

22:48.758 --> 22:51.413
♪ You can break through
the clouds ♪

22:51.457 --> 22:53.372
♪ Lift me up when I'm down

22:53.415 --> 22:54.677
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

22:54.721 --> 22:57.854
[ Chuckles ]
You're the fascinating stranger.

22:57.898 --> 22:59.421
What's your story?

22:59.465 --> 23:01.380
I...

23:01.423 --> 23:02.598
I don't really know.

23:02.642 --> 23:06.210
I guess I'm still
figuring it out.

23:06.254 --> 23:10.258
If you don't define you for you,
others will.

23:10.301 --> 23:13.566
The next time I see you,
you need an answer.

23:15.437 --> 23:16.830
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

23:16.873 --> 23:19.049
[ Laughs ]

23:19.093 --> 23:26.535
♪♪

23:26.579 --> 23:28.581
[ Chuckles ]

23:30.321 --> 23:31.714
[ Cellphone chimes ]

23:31.758 --> 23:32.933
Oh.

23:32.976 --> 23:35.892
[ Cellphone rings ]

23:35.936 --> 23:39.505
Nova, our office is buzzing

23:39.548 --> 23:41.724
from the ring shout protest
you did.

23:41.768 --> 23:44.292
Thank you. I'm still processing
the impact it had.

23:44.335 --> 23:46.512
So, the movie.

23:46.555 --> 23:49.950
The producers are just
champing at the bit.

23:49.993 --> 23:51.734
They want to get it
fast-tracked.

23:51.778 --> 23:55.651
So the team wants to come
to New Orleans to meet you.

23:55.695 --> 23:57.087
I see.

23:57.131 --> 23:59.263
You're still not thinking
of saying no?

23:59.307 --> 24:01.788
I need everyone in my family
to approve.

24:01.831 --> 24:03.267
All of them.

24:03.311 --> 24:05.531
And I haven't even asked,
with everything going on.

24:05.574 --> 24:10.318
Okay, Nova, this is
a once-in-a-lifetime offer.

24:10.361 --> 24:12.233
Ask them.
Work your magic.

24:12.276 --> 24:14.061
I'll try.

24:14.104 --> 24:15.323
Okay.

24:15.366 --> 24:17.151
Thanks.
We'll talk soon.

24:17.194 --> 24:19.066
[ Call disconnects ]

24:19.109 --> 24:20.371
[ Sighs ]

24:20.415 --> 24:22.591
[ Pop music playing ]

24:22.635 --> 24:27.291
Darla: Blue, being young
and Black and brilliant,

24:27.335 --> 24:28.858
the world is gonna
convince you

24:28.902 --> 24:31.513
that you're
breaking the rules

24:31.557 --> 24:33.863
when you're just
being yourself.

24:33.907 --> 24:35.604
But don't ever let it.

24:35.648 --> 24:37.954
♪ Love you the right way

24:37.998 --> 24:41.131
Well, now that I got
my computer back...

24:41.175 --> 24:42.785
Mm-hmm....if you want,

24:42.829 --> 24:45.222
I could build a website for
the co-op and Aunt Vi's Pies.

24:45.266 --> 24:46.572
I love that.

24:46.615 --> 24:48.051
She could pay me
in pies.

24:48.095 --> 24:50.140
No, get it in cash.

24:50.184 --> 24:52.012
Then I'll just buy pies.

24:52.055 --> 24:55.494
Darla Sutton?

24:55.537 --> 24:58.105
What are you doing
in DC?

24:58.148 --> 25:00.629
Look at you -- gorgeous.

25:00.673 --> 25:02.326
It's, um,
Darla Bordelon now,

25:02.370 --> 25:05.678
and this is my son,
Blue Bordelon.

25:09.159 --> 25:10.770
How old are you, Blue?

25:10.813 --> 25:12.728
I'm 11.

25:12.772 --> 25:14.034
Wow.

25:14.077 --> 25:16.036
Has it been 11 years
since we were in college?

25:16.079 --> 25:19.430
Um, Blue, can you go get us
some extra sprinkles?

25:19.474 --> 25:21.171
Get a lot.

25:21.215 --> 25:24.000
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

25:24.044 --> 25:27.264
♪♪

25:27.308 --> 25:30.790
Am I crazy?
He looks a lot like Chase.

25:30.833 --> 25:34.663
No. Uh, Ralph Angel
is Blue's father.

25:34.707 --> 25:39.494
I'm just saying,
you and Chase did have a moment.

25:41.801 --> 25:43.063
[ Sighs ]

25:43.106 --> 25:46.022
There was no moment.

25:46.066 --> 25:47.937
I was unconscious.

25:50.244 --> 25:52.115
I'm sosorry.

25:52.159 --> 25:53.464
I-I didn't know that.

25:53.508 --> 25:55.728
Wait, was it that night?

25:55.771 --> 25:57.556
The past is the past,
you know?

25:57.599 --> 25:59.470
I'm not looking back,
so...

25:59.514 --> 26:01.951
You know he's running
for Congress?

26:01.995 --> 26:04.258
There were rumors,
even back then.

26:04.301 --> 26:05.912
Please.

26:07.348 --> 26:09.742
Let it go.

26:13.093 --> 26:14.529
Hey.

26:14.573 --> 26:15.617
Mom?
Mm.

26:15.661 --> 26:17.227
You okay?
Yeah, yeah.

26:17.271 --> 26:18.402
Who was that?

26:18.446 --> 26:20.056
Just an old friend.
Here you go.

26:20.100 --> 26:22.450
Thanks.
Okay. Got it?

26:22.493 --> 26:25.409
[ Indistinct conversation ]

26:30.284 --> 26:32.242
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:32.286 --> 26:35.768
♪♪

26:35.811 --> 26:38.161
I thought it would
just be us bidding.

26:38.205 --> 26:39.859
Oh, don't worry.

26:39.902 --> 26:42.426
We got enough
to outbid everybody here.

26:44.646 --> 26:47.736
It's a good plan, Rah.

26:47.780 --> 26:49.782
The start
of something new.

26:49.825 --> 26:52.654
Ladies and gentlemen, up next,
we have a 100-acre plot

26:52.698 --> 26:54.395
of foreclosed farm land.

26:54.438 --> 26:56.571
Item C-24.

26:56.615 --> 26:59.052
I'd like to start the bidding
off at 200K.

26:59.095 --> 27:00.488
200K. 200?

27:00.531 --> 27:01.881
Thank you very much, sir.
$200 down right here.

27:01.924 --> 27:03.752
Now, who will give me 210?
210, anybody? 210.

27:03.796 --> 27:06.363
$210, down right here.
Now, who got 215?

27:06.407 --> 27:07.887
220, anybody?
220, right here,

27:07.930 --> 27:09.584
down right here.
Thank you very much, sir.

27:09.628 --> 27:12.239
220. Anybody, 230?
Anybody 230?

27:12.282 --> 27:14.371
$230 down right here.
230.

27:14.415 --> 27:15.677
Don't worry about it.

27:15.721 --> 27:17.331
How about 240, anybody?
240, anybody?

27:17.374 --> 27:19.855
240?
$240 down right here.

27:19.899 --> 27:22.336
240 going once,
going twice --

27:22.379 --> 27:24.904
700!

27:24.947 --> 27:29.343
I'll pay 700 for that gorgeously
maintained piece of land.

27:29.386 --> 27:31.824
[ Soft gasps and murmurs ]

27:35.305 --> 27:38.526
700 going once,
going twice.

27:38.569 --> 27:41.529
Sold to Landry Enterprises.

27:41.572 --> 27:44.140
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:46.142 --> 27:48.492
-Landry!
-Easy.

27:48.536 --> 27:49.755
Hey!

27:49.798 --> 27:52.671
You don't hear me
talking to you?

27:52.714 --> 27:55.804
The other day,
I had a drink in my hand,

27:55.848 --> 27:58.633
ready to unwind,
and I get a phone call

27:58.677 --> 28:01.070
telling me your ring shout
spooked the city council

28:01.114 --> 28:02.681
and they reversed
their decision --

28:02.724 --> 28:04.639
Parthena had nothing
to do with that.

28:04.683 --> 28:06.989
See, you Bordelons
never know

28:07.033 --> 28:10.297
when to leave
well enough alone.

28:10.340 --> 28:12.038
Maybe you learn today.

28:14.780 --> 28:17.478
Sorry about that,
Parthena.

28:18.305 --> 28:20.394
[ Car door opens ]

28:20.437 --> 28:24.006
[ Car door slams,
engine starts ]

28:24.050 --> 28:26.182
[ Car departs ]

28:26.226 --> 28:32.580
♪♪

28:32.623 --> 28:37.019
These old pictures of you
and Mom are just --

28:37.063 --> 28:40.283
I don't know if I'll ever
experience a love like this.

28:40.327 --> 28:46.028
I'm no angel, so if I can have
a second chance, so can you.

28:46.072 --> 28:47.551
Hmm.

28:47.595 --> 28:49.902
Ah.

28:49.945 --> 28:54.123
My wedding day to Claire was
the best day behind me,

28:54.167 --> 28:57.779
besides the day I held you
for the first time.

28:57.823 --> 28:59.041
Mm.

28:59.085 --> 29:01.087
Yeah.

29:02.915 --> 29:04.612
I don't want to
replace Claire.

29:07.180 --> 29:08.747
You're not, Daddy.

29:08.790 --> 29:11.227
She's still with us.

29:11.271 --> 29:13.752
And Sandy loves you.

29:13.795 --> 29:15.275
[ Both laugh ]

29:15.318 --> 29:17.973
So you got a lot more good days
in front of you.

29:18.017 --> 29:20.236
So do you.

29:20.280 --> 29:23.674
Why don't you give Vince
a second chance?

29:23.718 --> 29:26.677
Hell, he's here already.
How convenient is that?

29:26.721 --> 29:27.809
[ Chuckles ]

29:27.853 --> 29:30.072
You two don't quit,
do you?

29:30.116 --> 29:33.597
So, you're gonna be
at the potluck, right?

29:33.641 --> 29:34.947
I don't know.

29:34.990 --> 29:37.166
I think I'm gonna
stay home tonight.

29:37.210 --> 29:40.169
You gotta be there.
It's the first harvest.

29:40.213 --> 29:41.605
Please?

29:41.649 --> 29:44.260
Daddy, you got that look
in your eye.

29:45.740 --> 29:47.916
What you up to?

29:50.005 --> 29:51.833
So silly.

29:51.877 --> 29:53.313
♪ Getting pulled over

29:53.356 --> 29:56.403
♪ 'Cause there's someone else
I look like ♪

29:56.446 --> 29:59.188
♪ I'm scared

29:59.232 --> 30:01.060
Ignacio:
Vi. Thank God for you.

30:01.103 --> 30:03.540
How are the boys?
Are they okay?

30:03.584 --> 30:04.628
Are they eating?

30:04.672 --> 30:06.543
They are here,
they're safe,

30:06.587 --> 30:08.850
they're going to school,
don't you worry.

30:08.894 --> 30:11.287
Thank God.
Thank you, Vi.

30:11.331 --> 30:14.073
It's so hard to communicate
to anyone on the outside.

30:14.116 --> 30:16.379
'Nacio, how you holding up
in there, buddy?

30:16.423 --> 30:17.816
Everything okay?

30:17.859 --> 30:19.295
I'm okay.

30:19.339 --> 30:20.819
I just needed to know
my boys were safe.

30:20.862 --> 30:22.908
I can't lose them.

30:22.951 --> 30:25.084
Everyone here's trying
to find their children.

30:25.127 --> 30:26.955
They need to stay together.

30:26.999 --> 30:29.479
Please,
don't let them get lost.

30:29.523 --> 30:30.959
My church got me a lawyer,

30:31.003 --> 30:34.658
and she says that I can request
legal guardians.

30:34.702 --> 30:36.095
Of course, man.

30:36.138 --> 30:38.271
Look, they can stay here
as long as you need.

30:38.314 --> 30:39.881
Absolutely.

30:39.925 --> 30:43.363
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

30:43.406 --> 30:45.713
They're my everything.

30:45.756 --> 30:47.584
I know Bea is
trying to get back,

30:47.628 --> 30:50.152
but please
take care of them.

30:50.196 --> 30:54.243
We will, and I know
they really want to talk to you.

30:54.287 --> 30:56.332
Here you go.

30:56.376 --> 30:57.638
-Papa.
-Mijos.

30:57.681 --> 31:01.250
Papa.
You got through.

31:01.294 --> 31:02.686
We miss you so much.

31:02.730 --> 31:04.427
Mijos.

31:04.471 --> 31:06.299
Te amo much, mijos.

31:06.342 --> 31:08.692
[ Speaks Spanish ]

31:08.736 --> 31:09.868
Te amos también, Papa.

31:09.911 --> 31:12.348
[ Speaks Spanish ]

31:15.612 --> 31:16.787
So that's where the boys
will be sleeping,

31:16.831 --> 31:19.921
and we have, uh,
a couple of bed --

31:19.965 --> 31:23.055
twin beds that we're getting
from our neighbor,

31:23.098 --> 31:26.058
[chuckles]
and we got plentyof food.

31:26.101 --> 31:29.148
-Yeah. Plenty.
-Probably too much.

31:29.191 --> 31:32.412
Matter of fact, Joaquin is
always trying to get me

31:32.455 --> 31:33.979
to do more organic.

31:34.022 --> 31:35.241
Mm-hmm.

31:35.284 --> 31:37.112
Hmm.

31:45.860 --> 31:47.209
This will have to be
locked away.

31:47.253 --> 31:48.863
Oh, yeah, I'm putting
all that liquor up.

31:48.907 --> 31:50.865
All that's gone.
Now, the bottle of sherry --

31:50.909 --> 31:52.258
nobody's drinking that,
alright?

31:52.301 --> 31:53.433
Vi uses that for cooking.

31:53.476 --> 31:55.000
Doesn't matter.

31:55.043 --> 31:58.917
You'd be surprised
what these kids get into.

31:58.960 --> 32:00.701
Duly noted.

32:03.922 --> 32:07.099
I don't usually do it like this,
but the boys can stay with you

32:07.142 --> 32:08.839
while you complete
your application.

32:08.883 --> 32:11.712
If you pass, you're good to be
their temporary guardians.

32:11.755 --> 32:12.931
-That's great.
-Mm-hmm.

32:12.974 --> 32:15.194
Oh, what else
do you need?

32:15.237 --> 32:18.937
Just more paperwork
detailing income, employment,

32:18.980 --> 32:21.765
background checks on all adults
on the premises.

32:23.376 --> 32:24.986
All very standard.

32:25.030 --> 32:27.946
If there any other adults
living here besides you two?

32:30.513 --> 32:32.037
♪♪

32:32.080 --> 32:33.995
I gotta get you out
more often,

32:34.039 --> 32:36.389
this is how it's gonna be
when you get back.

32:36.432 --> 32:37.999
Stop it.

32:38.043 --> 32:41.742
And I really did
miss you.

32:41.785 --> 32:44.788
You held it down
all by yourself.

32:44.832 --> 32:47.487
I know those thirsty moms
at class were like,

32:47.530 --> 32:50.011
"Mm, is he single?"

32:50.055 --> 32:53.623
I mean,
maybe like one or two.

32:53.667 --> 32:55.582
Maybe three.
Mm-hmm.

32:55.625 --> 32:57.018
[ Baby coos ]

32:57.062 --> 33:00.021
She's fine.

33:00.065 --> 33:01.980
How was the rest
of the trip?

33:06.114 --> 33:07.507
Darla.

33:07.550 --> 33:09.335
The trip?

33:09.378 --> 33:11.598
I'm just tired.

33:12.468 --> 33:13.904
I'm good,

33:13.948 --> 33:15.602
now that I'm here
with you.

33:15.645 --> 33:18.039
♪♪

33:18.083 --> 33:20.955
Give me a kiss.

33:20.999 --> 33:22.739
Mm.

33:24.045 --> 33:27.788
Alright, more chicken,
everybody.

33:27.831 --> 33:30.617
Oh, no.
Is that Lucille?

33:30.660 --> 33:35.448
Oh, girl, what are you doing
at our first-harvest potluck?

33:35.491 --> 33:37.189
Prosper invited me
out the blue.

33:37.232 --> 33:39.626
Something about
miracles and love.

33:39.669 --> 33:41.062
I really
couldn't tell you.

33:41.106 --> 33:43.934
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, he's smitten.

33:43.978 --> 33:46.024
That's for sure.
[ Chuckles ]

33:47.851 --> 33:50.202
Now, hold on, ain't that
the little trollop

33:50.245 --> 33:52.987
that tried to steal
your husband back in the day?

33:53.031 --> 33:56.817
She at it again,
talking to your current husband.

33:56.860 --> 33:59.602
First, Hollywood's not
my current husband.

33:59.646 --> 34:02.388
Hollywood's
my forever husband.

34:02.431 --> 34:05.521
My equally yolked helpmate.

34:05.565 --> 34:06.827
Understand that?

34:06.870 --> 34:09.264
Second, all that mess
you're talking about

34:09.308 --> 34:11.353
was started by Jimmy Dale.

34:11.397 --> 34:16.532
Yeah, he was a grown man
chasing after young girls.

34:16.576 --> 34:19.970
He was the one
spreading that lie

34:20.014 --> 34:23.713
about that poor girl
hiking up her skirt.

34:26.890 --> 34:29.719
Do you think you can learn
anything from that?

34:29.763 --> 34:34.637
♪♪

34:35.551 --> 34:38.685
I left thinking, like,
"What have Idone?"

34:38.728 --> 34:39.860
[ Chuckles ]
I haven't been anywhere.

34:39.903 --> 34:41.035
Alright, man, we get it.

34:41.079 --> 34:42.645
Next year in Miami
at Art Basel.

34:42.689 --> 34:44.169
-Naw.
-We'll get lit.

34:44.212 --> 34:46.258
It's more than that.
Like, I want to break the mold.

34:46.301 --> 34:51.524
We spend all day chasing trends,
trying to make money, for what?

34:51.567 --> 34:54.135
What if we were
the new vanguard?

34:54.179 --> 34:56.442
You know, what if we walked in
and set the standard?

34:56.485 --> 34:58.487
[ Rap music playing ]
♪ A little bit childish

34:58.531 --> 35:01.882
Hey, guys, one more round
and we're out, alright?

35:01.925 --> 35:03.884
♪ I'm flying

35:03.927 --> 35:07.148
♪ Yo, yo, energy, energy,
energy, yo ♪

35:07.192 --> 35:10.804
♪♪

35:10.847 --> 35:14.634
Yo, you get what
I'm trying to say, right?

35:14.677 --> 35:16.070
[ Sighs ]

35:16.114 --> 35:18.725
Man, I'm --
I'm just confused,

35:18.768 --> 35:22.294
'cause you came to me
on some

35:22.337 --> 35:24.252
"Let's work together
as Black men" type tip.

35:24.296 --> 35:25.514
Yeah.

35:25.558 --> 35:27.995
I invest in you, and...

35:28.038 --> 35:30.171
you get lucky,
you make one sale.

35:32.086 --> 35:36.221
And now you're posting photos
that clash with our aesthetic.

35:36.264 --> 35:39.746
♪ Gimme the loop, hammer time,
gimme the truth, uh ♪

35:39.789 --> 35:42.444
[ R&B music plays ]

35:42.488 --> 35:45.143
[ Indistinct conversations ]

35:45.186 --> 35:53.716
♪♪

35:53.760 --> 36:02.551
♪♪

36:02.595 --> 36:03.987
You came.

36:06.076 --> 36:08.253
Your dad insisted that
that I not leave

36:08.296 --> 36:09.341
without saying goodbye.

36:09.384 --> 36:12.213
[ Chuckles ]
Right.

36:12.257 --> 36:14.346
Well, I'm really glad
you're here.

36:14.389 --> 36:16.478
Me, too.

36:16.522 --> 36:19.351
You wanna dance?

36:19.394 --> 36:20.526
Sure.

36:20.569 --> 36:22.702
[ Both chuckle ]

36:22.745 --> 36:26.358
♪♪

36:26.401 --> 36:28.186
May I?

36:28.229 --> 36:30.013
Of course.

36:31.667 --> 36:34.931
Look, I don't know

36:34.975 --> 36:37.369
how much time you need,

36:37.412 --> 36:40.241
but while you're taking it,
just --

36:40.285 --> 36:44.202
just know that, um,
I'm waiting.

36:45.420 --> 36:47.901
And I made myself okay
with our relationship

36:47.944 --> 36:49.990
being on your terms.

36:50.033 --> 36:52.906
I told myself it was fine.

36:52.949 --> 36:56.214
I've been telling myself
that for years.

36:58.216 --> 37:01.654
And...

37:01.697 --> 37:06.049
I-I'm gonna try to continue
to give you what you need now.

37:08.182 --> 37:11.185
What I learned
about your past,

37:11.229 --> 37:15.015
I understand
that it was traumatic

37:15.058 --> 37:17.235
and that you deserve
the room.

37:18.540 --> 37:20.107
Thank you.

37:21.630 --> 37:23.850
Look, man, I like you.

37:23.893 --> 37:27.375
Man, you're talented,
you're smart.

37:27.419 --> 37:29.159
[ Rap music playing ]

37:29.203 --> 37:34.252
But Ivory's not for everybody,
and that's okay.

37:34.295 --> 37:37.124
No matter what,
we'll always be cool.

37:37.167 --> 37:38.995
♪ I'm a little bit childish

37:39.039 --> 37:41.302
[ Scoffs ]

37:41.346 --> 37:44.262
♪ Chug another Red Bull down,
I'm flying ♪

37:44.305 --> 37:47.221
♪ Wild, wild renegade,
kill 'em with a smile ♪

37:47.265 --> 37:49.092
♪ High tide, overplayed

37:49.136 --> 37:50.529
[ Cellphone clicks open ]

37:50.572 --> 37:52.574
[ Buttons tapping ]

37:52.705 --> 37:55.969
Yo, Micah, we'll be late
for DeadGoat69's party.

37:56.012 --> 37:57.884
You coming?

37:57.927 --> 38:00.582
Uh, naw,
I'll meet y'all there.

38:00.626 --> 38:02.715
Okay.

38:02.758 --> 38:04.194
[ Door opens ]

38:04.238 --> 38:06.371
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:06.414 --> 38:10.940
♪♪

38:10.984 --> 38:12.464
This is the last time.

38:12.507 --> 38:15.510
[ R&B music plays ]

38:15.554 --> 38:17.817
If you choose us,

38:17.860 --> 38:20.733
things have to be
different.

38:20.776 --> 38:22.474
Verydifferent.

38:25.128 --> 38:28.131
So let that be part
of your decision.

38:28.175 --> 38:30.438
No more secrets.

38:30.482 --> 38:32.440
No more distance.

38:32.484 --> 38:34.529
You come back,

38:34.573 --> 38:36.792
we get married,

38:36.836 --> 38:39.055
and we grow together.

38:39.099 --> 38:41.928
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

38:43.408 --> 38:44.931
Or we don't.

38:44.974 --> 38:46.889
No more in between.

38:50.371 --> 38:51.764
Okay.

38:51.807 --> 38:59.554
♪♪

38:59.598 --> 39:07.345
♪♪

39:07.388 --> 39:14.917
♪♪

39:14.961 --> 39:22.664
♪♪

39:22.708 --> 39:24.753
[ Band playing up-tempo music ]

39:24.797 --> 39:32.326
♪♪

39:32.370 --> 39:39.725
♪♪

39:39.768 --> 39:47.123
♪♪

39:47.167 --> 39:49.648
Prosper Denton,
what are you doing?

39:49.691 --> 39:51.780
Come on.
Dance with me.

39:51.824 --> 40:01.050
♪♪

40:01.094 --> 40:10.538
♪♪

40:10.582 --> 40:19.852
♪♪

40:19.895 --> 40:22.724
[ Cheers and applause ]

40:25.640 --> 40:27.381
We're gathered here today
to celebrate

40:27.425 --> 40:30.689
the co-op's first harvest.

40:30.732 --> 40:32.125
[ Cheering ]

40:32.168 --> 40:33.474
Now, odds were against us,
but we made it here,

40:33.518 --> 40:38.131
and to me,
that is a miracle.

40:38.174 --> 40:39.959
[ Crowd agreeing ]

40:40.002 --> 40:42.701
And Sandy...

40:42.744 --> 40:44.442
you're my miracle.

40:44.485 --> 40:45.747
Oh.

40:45.791 --> 40:48.663
You've made me happier
than I've been in years.

40:48.707 --> 40:52.232
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

40:52.275 --> 40:54.713
And if you'll have me,

40:54.756 --> 40:57.367
I'd like to return the joy,
the passion,

40:57.411 --> 40:59.544
and the love
for as long as I can.

40:59.587 --> 41:02.764
♪♪

41:02.808 --> 41:04.810
-Oh. Oh!
-Okay!

41:04.853 --> 41:07.465
[ Laughter ]

41:09.249 --> 41:11.425
Sandy Leflore...

41:15.908 --> 41:18.432
...will you marry me?

41:18.476 --> 41:19.868
Yes, darling.

41:19.912 --> 41:21.914
I willmarry you.

41:21.957 --> 41:25.874
[ Cheers and applause ]

41:25.918 --> 41:27.528
[ Laughter ]

41:27.572 --> 41:30.618
[ Band playing up-tempo music ]

41:30.662 --> 41:38.887
♪♪

41:38.931 --> 41:47.156
♪♪

41:47.200 --> 41:55.600
♪♪

41:55.643 --> 42:05.044
♪♪

42:05.087 --> 42:08.482
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

42:08.526 --> 42:16.882
♪♪

42:16.925 --> 42:25.586
♪♪
